    "Current usage often includes all sources of attentional guidance other than goals and salience.",
    "The most studied selection history phenomena include inter-trial priming, statistical learning, learned associations between stimuli and outcomes (i.e., reward/punishment learning).",
    "Such guidance is typically considered to be driven by implicit mechanisms.",
    "Set size The number of stimuli in a search display.",
    "Singleton A stimulus that has a (locally) unique feature in any feature dimension."
